deck: The Mighty Mr. Spook travels the Beanworld trying to discover the secret of the Mystery Pods.  He meets various characters like The Boom'R Band and Beanish.
description:
Mr. Spook is attempting to open a pod, but it resists all attempts. The Boom'r Band attempts to explain the problem, but their odd lingo only confuses him further. Even though the tools he tried to use were damaged, Mr. Spook is undeterred. On the way to figure out a way to open the mystery pod Mr. Spook runs into Beanish who is busy creating his latest Look-See Show titled Proffy. Beanish locates a powerful being that won't tell Beanish its name, floating in the sky. Beanish is ordered not to tell anyone about how to find this individual. Because Beanish promises to keep its existence secret they can be friends.

The mystery pods create two distinct sounds so an attempt is made to use the Boom'r Bands methods and powers to determine what is inside. They create music with it, but because it's from a mystery pod Mr. Spook orders the Boom'r Band to stop playing. They continue playing despite Mr. Spook's concerns. Their new sound is named The Clang Twang!

Beanish' audience is missing because they're discovering The Clang Twang. The action moves to the center of Beanlife -- great Gan'Ma'Pa. The beans dance themselves into a long sleep. To wake them up a bean falls from the Gan'Ma'Pa (which is a large tree) and the new bean tells Mr. Spook to make him angry so he can wake up the beans. They need to be up to collect some Chow from dazed Hoi-Polloi. This does not happen because the beans are still out cold. Mr. Spook and the rest of the beans learn their lesson and vow to never play the Clang Twang again.

The dancing also caused Beanish to sleep through his appointment. He makes it late, and falls in love with his floating unnamed being.
name: Yeah, Yeah! The Clang Twang

deck: Dead America: Know Your Enemy (Gold) from DeadZone Comics
description: Black Ops operative Dameon Spikes is one of the few, remaining human survivors left after a nuclear blast augmented with a biochemical nerve gas has changed the landscape of America. Now, the country is over-populated with infected citizens that have been altered into flesh eating ZOMBIES! Spikes ongoing mission is to protect human survival, but he's also on a personal crusade to find out who was behind this catastrophic turn of events that ravaged the country that he loves...and then make them pay. What will Spikes do when he finds himself face to face with the architect of this new world order...in a shocking turn of events that he never thought could be possible.
name: Know Your Enemy

description: Dr. Octopus! Electro! Mysterio! The Vulture! The Hobgoblin! Sandman! The Sinister Six, the deadliest foes Spider-Man has ever fought, return to wreak terrible vengeance upon our favorite wall-crawler - and an unsuspecting world. With Dr. Octopus' new Adamantium arms and help from another dimension on the Six's side, Spidey decides to round up his own band of allies: the Hulk, Ghost Rider, the Fantastic Four and more! It all adds up to the ultimate high-stakes faceoff in a sock-to-the-jaw adventure that will leave you breathless - if you and Spider-Man can make it to the thrill-packed finale in one piece! Plus: a bonus story co-starring the X-Men's Beast! Collecting SPIDER-MAN (1990) #15 and #18-23.
